  "description": "These sparrows were typically identified by their musical 'te-da-da-deeeeeeee' song.\u00a0 They had necklaces and olive/buffy heads that were patterned.\u00a0 We found one pair with fledged young in Larimer County in mid-June, and an active nest in Weld County in early August.\u00a0 We color banded 11 individual birds between June and July.",
